Version:          1.0
Release:          3%{?dist}%{?buildtag}
Summary:          Item Analysis for Multiple Choice Tests

License:          GPL (>= 2)
URL:              https://cran.r-project.org/package=%{packname}
Source0:          %{url}&version=%{packver}#/%{packname}_%{packver}.tar.gz


BuildRequires:    R-devel
Requires:         R-core
BuildArch:        noarch
BuildRequires:    R-CRAN-ggplot2 
BuildRequires:    R-CRAN-reshape 
Requires:         R-CRAN-ggplot2 
Requires:         R-CRAN-reshape 

%description
Functions for analyzing multiple choice items. These analyses include the
convertion of student response into binaty data (correct/incorrect), the
computation of the number of corrected responses and grade for each
subject, the calculation of item difficulty and discrimination, the
computation of the frecuency and point-biserial correlation for each
distractor and the graphical analysis of each item.

